    "Convergence: The eyes move toward each other when viewing a close object. 2.",
    "Divergence: The eyes move away from each other when viewing a distant object.",
    "Discrepancies between real and simulated vergence movements can lead to discomfort or motion sickness.",
    "• Nystagmus: A vision condition characterized by involuntary, repetitive eye movements.",
    "These movements often result in reduced or limited vision as the eyes uncontrollably oscillate in a quick, jerky, or pendular manner."
